725581f-a.text:
69th Street, at 63rd Avenue (vantage point), viewing northeastward from an elevation across Middle Village.
P. L. Sperr  July 7, 1940

725579f-d.text:
At the N.E. corner of Sixty-ninth Avenue and Queens Boulevard, showing the four views of the Ascan Bakus house. In 1923 the Cord Meyer Development Company was the owner. Oscar William Christian Backus was born in 1814 and came to this country in 1829. He died March 18, 1880. He married Mary A. Beetham. A daughter, Mary Eliza, married in 1874 Dr. Howard Lever.

April 1923.
Views 1 and 2.
View 3: March 1925.
View 4: October 1928.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
